  <h2>What Makes This Different</h2>
  <p>When you list with a Realtor, you're waiting for a buyer to get financing, pass inspections, and not change their mind. With a cash buyer, there's no middleman and no uncertainty. We can often close within 7–10 days — fast enough to get ahead of most foreclosure timelines.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Cash offer within 24 hours</li>
    <li>Close in as little as 7–10 days</li>
    <li>No repairs or cleaning needed</li>
    <li>No commissions or fees</li>
    <li>Potential to walk away with cash even in a tough situation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Honest Trade-Off</h2>
  <p>A cash offer will typically be below full retail market value — that's the trade-off for speed, certainty, and zero prep costs. But when you factor in commissions (5–6%), repair costs, carrying costs during a 60–90 day listing, and the risk of deals falling through — a fair cash offer often puts more money in your pocket than you'd expect.</p>
  <p>We'll always give you a straight answer. If the traditional route is actually better for your situation, we'll tell you that.</p>

